<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1915-04-01T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1915-04-01T00:00:00-05:00" n="1520" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1520">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.404/62.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                Consul <persName type="to">Schmutz</persName></hi>.</head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 90.]</seg>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1915-04-01">
                                    <hi rend="italic">April 1, 1915</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: The Department has received your despatch
                            No. 258 of February 12, 1915, reporting that three Spanish priests
                            [etc.]</p>
                        <p>The Department approves of your action in sending the telegram to Mr.
                            George C. Carothers asking him to see General Villa and try to have the
                            order rescinded.</p>
                        <p>It also approves of your action in giving certain letters to the Spanish
                            Vice Consul for presentation to the three consular officers between
                            Aguascalientes and El Paso, should it be necessary to request any aid of
                            them.</p>
                        <p>I am [etc.]</p>
                        <closer>For the Secretary of State: <lb/>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Wilbur J. Carr.</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>